cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for automated colorization of grayscale images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method involves training a conditional PixelCNN and a second CNN, which are both machine learning models, indicating a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using human raters to judge the quality of the colorizations, suggesting a potential fit for the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which could potentially fit under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
